# Discord Bot Token
# Get your token from https://discord.com/developers/applications
# Copy this file to .env and add your actual bot token
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here

# Discord Client ID
# Get your client ID from https://discord.com/developers/applications
# This is the Application ID shown in the General Information section
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here

# Discord Bot Permissions Required
# When inviting the bot to your server, you need to grant the following permissions:
# 
# Required Permissions:
# - Use Application Commands (Required for slash commands)
# - Send Messages (Required to respond to commands)
# - View Channels (Required to interact in channels)
#
# Optional but Recommended Permissions:
# - Embed Links (Recommended for formatted status messages)
# - Read Message History (Optional but may be useful for context)
# - Use External Emojis (Optional, for enhanced status displays)
#
# Minimum Permissions Integer: 274878024704
# 
# To invite the bot:
# 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Select your application
# 3. Go to OAuth2 > URL Generator
# 4. Select scopes: "bot" and "applications.commands"
# 5. Select the permissions listed above (or use the permissions integer)
# 6. Copy the generated URL and open it in your browser
# 7. Select your server and authorize
